-Also, for the time range that they examine, effects from ecology leading to frequency-dependent selection can be ignored.
-beneficial mutations observed were ~20,000 in E1 and ~11,000 in E2 for muations of low effect (2-5%), and 5,000 in E1 and 3,000 in E2 of large effect (~10%)      

ORGANISM (Saccharomyces cerevisiae):
-Eukaryotic fungus that can be haploid or diploid (preferential form), and reproduce in either state through mitosis 
