-ancestors have spontaneous mutation rate in non repeated regions ~4e-10
-the trajectories in fig 2a are most illustrative of the experiment in terms of what data was collected.  Every 8 gens the frequencies are measured and used to extrapolate their cell count as a function of time.  These are the red trajectories shown in the figure.
-section 11.1 in the supplement provides the way in which they inferred mutation rates for given selection coeff size, but there seem to be some typos and unclear steps in the derivation of formula 101.  Just move forward and maybe ask about it later.
