METHOD FOR ESTIMATING TAU AND S: 
1) develop a model for noise to account for the behavior of drift causing a lineage to fix, or measurement errors in sequencing
2) use model of noise and calculate probability that trajectory explained by mutation with fitness effect s having established time tau, over broad range of pairs (i.e. using prior distrib)
3) if above probability exceeds probability that no beneficial mutation occurs, define the trajectory as adaptive
