Wilkinson 1990 compared L(y_A,(G_A ) ̂ ) with L(y_A,(G_B ) ̂) (likelihoods of y_A given estimates (G_A ) ̂ and (G_B ) ̂, which is wrong because it ignores sampling variation in (G_B ) ̂.  Here L(y_A,G ̂) is the likelihood of the data y_A given G ̂.
	
